                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I am throwing this out to you as ideas to reduce the risk of charm in the Omens of War expansion, since it is rather apparent from the few comments made by SOE on this subject that they are satisfied with what they did to the benefits of charm.
<br />

<br />
#1 Perform the "charm break" resist check only when the monster is attacking.
<br />

<br />
The idea here is that the charmed monster is enthralled with the enchanters and will happily follow the enchanter around, doing his or her bidding for simple commands such as "come here," "stay put," or "sit down." However, if the enchanter commands the monster to attack another monster, suddenly it is in conflict, because it might be risking its life to perform this command.  So give the monster a chance to resist charm while it is attacking and only while it is attacking.
<br />

<br />
Charm will still wear off as normal like any other debuff, and the enchanter will be required to recharm or deal with the monster in some other manner.
<br />

<br />
This idea has the additional benefit of allowing enchanters to go AFK while not engaged in combat, rather than having to spend every second minding their charmed pet.  This gives the enchanter the ability to enjoy group downtime without risk, same as the other players in their group, but within reason -- charm only lasts 75 ticks.  I think any enchanter who has ever charmed for an extended period of time can appreciate this feature.
<br />

<br />
Important:  Do not increase this "charm break" resist chance just because the monster can no longer resist charm when not engaged in combat.  The idea here is to reduce the risk of charm to match the reduced benefits of charming, not to make charm so inviable that no one will ever use it for combat ever again.
<br />

<br />
#2 Allow enchanters to refresh charm.
<br />

<br />
This is a simple, already (though seldomly) suggested, idea.  Reward enchanters attentive enough to keep track of their charm's nominal duration (75 ticks) with the ability to refresh their charms.  This is already possible if an enchanter dispels charm and then recharms, but there is risk involved when doing this because of resists, fizzles, dispelled debuffs, etc.
<br />

<br />
This goes hand in hand with #1, allowing enchanters to go AFK without having to go through the rigmarole of dispeling and recharming just because charm is due to wear off sooner than they can return to their keyboards to resume play.
<br />

<br />
#3 Allow debuffs by players in the enchanter's group to land on charmed pets.
<br />

<br />
Allowing players in group to refresh their debuffs on a charmed pet goes hand in hand with #2.  Currently, the only way for a debuffer to refresh their debuff on a charmed pet is for charm to break or for the enchanter to dispel charm.  Note that this is already possible on PvP servers where players can cast detrimental spells on other players (and presumably the charmed pets of these players).
<br />

<br />
Naturally, this should include the enchanter too (MR debuff is important for maintaining charm).
<br />

<br />
Give the charmed monster a resist check every time someone attempts to debuff it.  The idea is that the charmed monster is disturbed by the notion of his friend's allies attempting to do harm to it.
<br />

<br />
Important:  Do not allow any debuffs with damage components to land on charmed pets.  This is to prevent the exploit of players being able to bring their charmed pet to near death without it making any attempt to defend itself.  Have charm break automatically as soon as someone in group does damage to it.
<br />

<br />
Actually, I recommend making these changes for charm in any expansion, not just Omens; however, because of the amount of risk reduced by doing so, SOE would be required to reduce the benefits of charming in pre-Omens content, something they already allegedly said they've no intention of doing.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=824212" target="_blank" class="postlink">Visionary Provender</a>, High Elf Coercer (retired)
<br />
<a href="http://www.therunes.net/forums/viewtopic.php?p=18979" target="_blank" class="postlink">E67.154/TT h+ 2.9khp 4.8km ft12 !G&gt;&lt;3 e++(+++) o++ T+++ L++ H++(+++) f- g+ b- c++(+++) t+ D- !X</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
