                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I like that we're all thinking of solutions, but I have to say that the three fixes you have proposed would make charming a lot less of a thrill. Not that it's all that thrilling anymore anyhow.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I empathize, but can you have the thrill without the high reward as well as the high risk? Charm in OoW is currently high risk, low reward, and thus dead. We can fix that by either going back to high risk, high reward, or by going to low risk, low reward.
<br />

<br />
My read of what little SOE has told us suggests that there's simply no way they're going to increase charmed pet DPS back to previous levels, and I really doubt they'll go any higher than where they are now. That's why I think we ought to push for decreased risk, though I certainly would support increased reward if we could get it.
<br />

<br />
And sadly, the result will be less of a thrill. Personally I find the thrill doesn't last long and after a long charm session I feel like I need some way to unwind--which isn't exactly what I look for in a recreational activity. But I do empathize with people who really do enjoy charming and think SOE's decision to destroy what they love about the game stinks.
<br />

<br />
The thrill died when SOE decided to reduce the reward of charming. Reducing the risk will at least make it usable again.
<br />

<br />
Teremar Talfirien</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
