                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I like "confused loyalties," except that the charmed pet will still attack at its unbalanced dps rate when the debuff isn't active.  I don't think SOE will go for that.
<br />

<br />
How about making it so that slow does not affect a pet while it is charmed?
<br />

<br />
That way you can slow a pet before charming it and have it attack at its normal attack rate while charmed.  When charm breaks, it is slowed and "just another add."
<br />

<br />
The standard debuff package prior to charming something would be tash, malo, snare (if snareable), and slow.  You could dispel charm, and it would still be slowed since slow has disease counters.  Slow wears off over time, of course, but so do tash, malo, and snare.
<br />

<br />
It places the onus of making the pet manageable on us rather than making us rely on a proc that may or may not wear off in 0-3 ticks.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=824212" target="_blank" class="postlink">Visionary Provender</a>, High Elf Coercer (retired)
