                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I like "confused loyalties," except that the charmed pet will still attack at its unbalanced dps rate when the debuff isn't active. I don't think SOE will go for that. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
First, you can have loyalties go off on every swing, period.  Proc rates can be upped that much.
<br />

<br />
Second, the charm-DPS nerf can be on during the union of "charm" and "confused loyalties effect".  If the mob is charmed, or if it's loyalties are confused...
<br />

<br />
Third, you could have "confused loyalties effect" be a "trigger-on-fade" of charm.  It is cast when charm fades, much like our epic boggle effect.  We get 2 to 3 ticks to deal with the reduced-DPS pet.
<br />

<br />
Altneratively, they could:
<br />
1&gt; Add 1% slow and -100% dual wield skill to charm spells (prevent DW and haste)
<br />
2&gt; Roll back most of the 'max hit' charm mitigation nerf.  The DPS enchanters are supposed to be doing is based off dual wielding hasted pets.  Now they can base it off non-DWing non-hasted pets (currently, a non-DW non-hasted OOW pet does about 50% more dps than our animation, which works out to zero increase in group xp rate because the pet steals nearly the same amount of xp).  Charm pet max hit can be increased by a factor of 3 to 4.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
