I suspect that Color Snap will make things workable, especially in light of the apparent fact that most mobs seem to proc a DoT (making WoM hit-or-miss).  Of course, this is part of the fun for me--deciding on the fly which of my memmed spells best fits the situation at hand (and this is one of the things which highlights an enchanters true skill).  I just wish that I didn't have to work through 4 Greater Muramite Runes to get to it.  Compel charming should be entertaining in close-quarters--glad I have a cleric for a 2-box...
