I still want a WoM upgrade, AND the exp nerf REMOVED.
<br />

<br />
You know, I think that reverse-charming in a lvl 68+ expedition will be half-decent exp...a shaman and I were comparing the exp gain on root/rotting, but I couldn't charm anything high enough (at that time--I just dinged 68 yesterday, before work, but had all of my spells waiting for me...BOOM...3k+ crit...everytime...<img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> for comparison purposes...I will try this out on my next night off.  As it is, I went from 5 ticks of regular exp per clearing of HS (in HoH...the southern one, or Hero Shu-rine...<img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />, to half that by dinging 68.  Fortunately, AAexp on my cleric is untouched, but this does hurt a bit...one more old stomping ground a thing of the past...
