                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Baalazai wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
While this seems great at first, the potential to abuse this is huge.  Imagine enc charming a mob, and then breaking charm immediately after so that the mob has reduced dps.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This has already been discussed too.   Once of the proposed solutions to the potential abuse of this would be that if any damage at all was done to the mob right after a charm break, then the mob would revert to hitting for full damage.  If no damage was being done, the mob would retain it's "rez-like affects" for a limited amount of time</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
